  "texts": [
    "In contrast to the relatively extensive studies on PR estimators, research on training methods for PR remains scarce.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, four studies Wang et al. (2021); Robey et al.",
    "(2022); Zhang et al.",
    "(2024a; 2025) explicitly motivated to develop training methods for improving PR.",
    "The first three can be categorized as Risk-based Training (RT) methods, which shift away from the worst-case perspective towards a training paradigm based on statistical risks induced by distributional perturbations, incorporating perturbation risk functions into the objective."
  ],
